Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Interpreting the Solutions for a Particle in a Box", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8087515127805104`*^9, 
  3.8087515198814354`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d0f4f361-2c01-4a34-b61f-\
b68d96955267"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Energy of a Particle in a Box is Quantized", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.808751536571563*^9, 
  3.8087515494986105`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"009a4d5d-13ab-4fef-bef7-\
3e4f4f05712e"],

Cell["\<\
We saw above that the energy values for a particle in a box are given by\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809352246411604*^9, 
  3.8093522764629917`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"76c447c8-92d4-4f4a-8d4e-\
0b26621352c5"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["E",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["n",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["n",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
    SuperscriptBox["\[Pi]", "2"], 
    SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"]}], 
   RowBox[{"2", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["ma",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]}]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.808746256152788*^9, 3.8087463361701956`*^9}, {
  3.808746369787464*^9, 
  3.808746370563246*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f772d194-170b-44b4-879a-\
0c5be10963bb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "meaning that the energy only has discrete values and no other values. \
Simply as a result of imposing boundary conditions, we have constrained the \
energy of the particle. When we encounter equations like this in quantum \
mechanics, we often refer to ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " as a quantum number. In lesson 01, we noted that Planck had asserted that \
energy must be quantized in integer values to explain blackbody radiation. We \
now know that the quantization of energy levels is a direct result of finding \
solutions to the time-independent Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger equation, and these \
numbers don\[CloseCurlyQuote]t have to be inserted without explanation."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809352309416527*^9, 3.8093525942957487`*^9}, {
  3.915643270866127*^9, 
  3.9156432818337374`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b6b68d11-9163-4f6e-b5e8-\
5163d086446d"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Lowest-Energy State doesn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t have an Energy of \
Zero", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8087515821530495`*^9, 
  3.8087516284279795`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"178aadd6-1543-4fc5-a56b-\
2fef897cc200"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If we solve the equation for the allowed energy levels for ",
 StyleBox["n",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " = 1, we find that"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8093526435224543`*^9, 
  3.8093527024865723`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6c9ac600-b9db-4c5f-929a-\
79d0cecae6d9"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["E",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"], "=", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["\[Pi]", "2"], 
    SuperscriptBox["\[HBar]", "2"]}], 
   RowBox[{"2", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["ma",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]}]]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.808746256152788*^9, 3.8087463361701956`*^9}, {
  3.808746369787464*^9, 3.808746370563246*^9}, {3.80935270912554*^9, 
  3.8093527190852757`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5229dff7-0a18-414a-952c-\
7f4abc12af43"],

Cell["\<\
In other words, the lowest allowed energy state of a particle in a box is not \
equal to zero. For quantum mechanical systems, the energy of this lowest, or \
ground, state is typically called the zero-point energy. It is, again, a \
natural consequence of finding the solutions of the TISE, but it is also \
consistent with the Heisenberg uncertainty principle, because an energy of \
zero would imply that the particle\[CloseCurlyQuote]s position and momentum \
are both known exactly.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809352723709833*^9, 3.809352740229596*^9}, {
  3.809352791794917*^9, 3.8093529220634317`*^9}, {3.8093529718164864`*^9, 
  3.8093530055039654`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c893d50c-c55b-4a63-85b8-\
966970363ad5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
The Absolute Square of the Wavefunction gives us Location Probability\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.808751608466797*^9, 
  3.8087516509208994`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"90d91f4c-408d-4826-b844-\
95875f891177"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Since we have properly normalized our wavefunction, we can now say that the \
probability that an object in the state specified by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "711d15a5-763a-4bae-8213-db3138e4bec1"],
 "(",
 StyleBox["x",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ")  will be found in the volume element ",
 StyleBox["dx",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " located at ",
 StyleBox["x",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is given by"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8093531759399176`*^9, 3.809353243166479*^9}, 
   3.840802788420664*^9},ExpressionUUID->"49d3ead0-5946-46db-b3a0-\
59096fb7ec2c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SuperscriptBox["\[Psi]", "\[Star]"], 
  RowBox[{"(", 
   StyleBox["x",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], "\[Psi]", 
  RowBox[{"(", 
   StyleBox["x",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox[")",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
  StyleBox["dx",
   FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8079664251944246`*^9, 3.8079664343142004`*^9}, {
   3.8079689400739555`*^9, 3.8079689680029573`*^9}, {3.807970315263204*^9, 
   3.8079703215316095`*^9}, {3.807970415909548*^9, 3.807970437015459*^9}, {
   3.8079705221296997`*^9, 3.8079705895237727`*^9}, {3.8079740353167067`*^9, 
   3.807974091342613*^9}, {3.8079792460635405`*^9, 3.807979253256398*^9}, {
   3.808056638763859*^9, 3.808056681287653*^9}, 3.808056968998802*^9, {
   3.8080571290891876`*^9, 3.8080571901776743`*^9}, 3.8080573054165645`*^9, {
   3.808062673780108*^9, 3.808062685868935*^9}, {3.8093532613187714`*^9, 
   3.8093532697922363`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cf45ab7a-c844-4d9c-94c9-\
aed3198de49f"],

Cell["in accordance with the first postulate of quantum mechanics.", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8093532761588*^9, 
  3.8093532931908755`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"60849a72-a90a-40e3-b855-\
9bdb2ac34716"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In other words, we can calculate the probability of finding the particle in \
the interval ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["x", "1"], "\[LessEqual]", "x", "\[LessEqual]", 
    SubscriptBox["x", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c6cb956b-3643-4b5f-9f15-4a0d67579eaa"],
 " as"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809353300003901*^9, 
  3.809353383473883*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8ecaff43-d2ab-4a9d-aa19-\
692014d20cbe"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  SubsuperscriptBox["\[Integral]", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["x",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"], 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["x",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]], 
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["\[Psi]", "\[Star]"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["x",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], ")"}], "\[Psi]", 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    StyleBox["x",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
   StyleBox["dx",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
